\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  * All spells and spell macros now use priority system to priority order received.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  * Added priority system to macro system.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  * You can use "Auto-Spell-Check" feature by pressing both the macro tab and the spell checking button simultaneously. Now both buttons can be pressed simultaneously.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  * Added "Enable All Stacks" option, which automatically adjusts all your spell critical strike chance, melee critical strike chance, and total critical strike chance to the appropriate value.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  * Macros and key bindings are now saved server-side so there is no longer a need to reconfigure them when logging in using another computer.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  * Spell Haste: Spell Haste now has a checkbox that can be checked when the spell buff is about to expire. This will prevent the haste % from being prematurely triggered when casting a spell that already has a duration.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  * Auto-save feature has been added to the game and is now available in all skillful specializations. This feature will automatically save the specialization percentage of your profession/trinket when you log in each day. You can still select the checkbox to check out the current specialization when you want to change your mind and/or replace a lost specialization.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  * You can now re-specialize in a profession by visiting an NPC in the city or logging out with the NPC in your party. You can do this from within the profession UI or by clicking on the profession icon on the world map. Once you have done this you can still re-specialize in the same way you normally would have, by clicking on the re-specialize button on the trade window.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  * Re-specialization: A feature that allows you to change the look of your secondary profession/trinket by visiting an NPC has been added.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  * You can now assign skill points to multiple recipes. This feature can be accessed via the profession UI by clicking on the "Skill Points" button next to the "Recipe" or "Selected Recipes" button, or by clicking on the "Skill Points" button in the upper right corner of the portrait. Multiple profession/trinkets can be assigned skill points on the same recipe, but the feature only works for recipes with skill points up for reagent crafting currently.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  * Reagent crafting now has a reagent cap. To account for the additional random element required to get all the ingredients to a reagent, the cap has been increased to 50.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  * You can now assign skill points to multiple recipes that require less reagents, by visiting an NPC in the city or logging in with the NPC in your party. You will not be able to use this feature for recipes that require gold, silver, or copper.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  * Multiple reagents can be assigned skill points on the same recipe, but the reagent cap has been increased to 50.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  * Gold, silver, and copper will no longer be awarded for the same recipe if a player obtains both the materials by a specific combination. For example, if a player obtains both gold and copper from a recipe and then silver from another recipe, the silver will be awarded first, followed by gold.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  * Players will no longer be able to use the "Refresh All" button to refresh an arena team before a scheduled game. The Refresh All button appears when a team is due a forfeit and will not refresh when a team has not been due a forfeit.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  * Players will no longer be able to use the "Random Matchmaking" feature to queue for a specific game type under specific restrictions. For example, someone who attempts to queue for Conquest of the Eastern Plaguelands or Battle for Azeroth PvP will be placed into a queue for PvP only Azeroth games, or for a time when the PvP cap is reached.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  * Random Matchmaking: In addition to allowing players to queue for specific games, players can now randomly find opponents with the Random option in either scenario. When playing against someone randomly, the Random option will always show as available, regardless of any previous opponents that may have been in the queue.}
