\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       One of the most talked about changes in the WoW game has been the Alignment system. The entire game has been redesigned to be less intuitive, more accessible, and more intuitive. We've broken down the Alignment system into 4 different phases: Pre-Alignment, Alignment, Post-Alignment, and Flexibility.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       Before we talk about how this change affects you, let's first clarify what exactly this is. The Pre-Alignment phase allowed you to make tough calls about which expansion to support. We're pretty sure most players found that the Alignment they chose was no different than the previous version, but hey, it was a change!}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       So, what does it do? It smooths out the initial announcement of an expansion by giving players a reason to want to support it. It also helps players avoid making the wrong choice between an expansion and a random pre-release build.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0        * Pre-Alignment }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0           * Alignment points now determine which pre-release content you get to in each patch. Points can be earned for Honorable Kills, which means "for which realm" the bonus content is applied.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0           * Points can be earned for completing specific objectives, both inside and outside of the game.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0           * Alignment points are no longer based on realm power or account bonuses. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0               * For Honorable Kills, characters earn extra points based on the modifiers of each bonus.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0               * For example, a character who earns 2400 Alignment points for completing the objectives of "A Feast for the Seven" receives a 2400 Alignment bonus instead of a normal 2400.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0              }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0              }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0           * After the official announcement of an expansion, updates on how the content will be received quickly follow.}
